{{Infobox language |name=Wiarumus |nativename=Mandi |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |region=[[East Sepik Province]] |ethnicity=460 (2000 census)<ref name=e18>{{e18|tua|Wiarumus}}</ref> |speakers=160 |date=1981 |ref=e15 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]] |fam2=[[Marienberg languages|Marienberg]] |fam3= |iso3=tua |glotto=wiar1238 |glottorefname=Wiarumus }}
'''Wiarumus''', a.k.a. '''Mandi''', is a [[Torricelli languages|Torricelli language]] of [[Papua New Guinea]], spoken in a village of just under 500. Only those villagers born before ca. 1940 can speak it.
== External links == * [[Paradisec]] has two open access collections that include Wiarumus language materials; the first is [[Donald Laycock|Don Laycock]]'s ([http://catalog.paradisec.org.au/collections/DL2 DL2]), the second is [[William A. Foley|William Foley]]'s ([http://catalog.paradisec.org.au/collections/WF3 WF3])
